#Solana does not have 1.6M daily active users. This is the number of active addresses.

Active addresses can be divided into send addresses and receive addresses.

1 transaction needs at least 2 addresses.

It is possible to make one group out of them. Roughly 800K addresses belong to senders and 800K to recipients.

One user can own multiple addresses and send multiple transactions daily from a new address.

If, for example, 1 user owned 10 addresses, there would be only 80K senders.

If both sender and recipient generate a new address for each transaction, it has a similar effect.

If 1 user sends 10 transactions per day to 1 recipient who generates a new recipient address each time, 20 addresses will be needed.

Only 2 users will generate 20 daily active addresses for statistics.

About 1M new addresses are generated daily on Solana. It indicates a low reuse of addresses.

90% of transactions on Solana are generated by bots.

Bot transactions need addresses.

Bots can generate a large number of daily active addresses.

If we consider that only 10% of active addresses belong to real users, that is 160K (80K transactions).

That would be the maximum amount possible. If each user sent 10 transactions, that would only be 16K active users. 

This is a similar amount to other blockchains including #Cardano.

Everything about Solana is fake, so it's hard to believe anything.

There is no active community so it is hard to believe that there are 1,6M daily active users. It is very unlikely.
